<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880902-0078 </DOCNO><HL> First City Bancorp. Texas Fires 2 Aides, Alleges They Stole Mail </HL><SO> </SO><CO> FBT </CO><G> JUS </G><DATELINE> HOUSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   First City Bancorp. of Texas said it fired two mailroom employees for allegedly stealing registered mail from the mailroom of its Dallas bank.    The banking concern said &quot;outside conspirators&quot; may also have been involved in the scheme, and said it is cooperating with the Federal Bureau of Investigation in trying to determine the extent of the theft. Neither First City, nor the FBI would comment on how much money might have been involved.    The company also said the U.S. attorney's office has referred the matter to a federal grand jury in Dallas.    A company spokesman wouldn't elaborate on the investigation. </TEXT></DOC>